				<text>13.4.1.5 Integration by parts</text>
		</name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p>
<p>Find</p>
<p>\({\displaystyle\int {@exp4@} \, \mathrm{d}x} = \) [[input:ans4]] [[validation:ans4]] [[feedback:prt4]]</p>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p>We apply integraton by parts:
  \[ \int u \frac{dv}{dx} \, \mathrm{d}x = uv - \int \frac{du}{dx} v \, \mathrm{d}x, \]
or alternatively:
  \[\int f(x)g(x) \, \mathrm{d}x = f(x) \, \int g(x) \mathrm{d}x - \int \frac{df}{dx} \left\{\int g(x) \, \mathrm{d}x \right\} \, \mathrm{d}x. \]
</p>
<p>We are given the integral \({\displaystyle\int {@exp4@} \, \mathrm{d}x}\).</p>
<p>We have \( f(x) = {@f4@}\) and \(g(x) = {@g4@}\).</p>
<p>Hence:
  \[\begin{aligned} \int {@exp4@} \, \mathrm{d}x &amp;=({@f4@}) \int {@g4@} \, \mathrm{d}x -\int \left({@df4@} \cdot \int {@g4@} \, \mathrm{d}x \right) \, \mathrm{d}x \\ &amp;= {@f4* intg4@}- \int {@df4*intg4@} \, \mathrm{d}x \\ &amp;= {@ta4@}. \end{aligned}\]
</p>]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
